text.tspan: I on behalf of our organization committe take immense pleasure in
inviting Professor Douglass Scott to attend the inauguration function of
our new exhibition about Leshan Giant Buddha in Museum of Fine Arts
on Boston, Massachutes. The inauguration will begin at April 13, 2017.
The theme of the exhibition is Leshan Giant Buddha in Mount Emeri
Scenic Area in China. The Leshan Giant Buddha is a 71-metre (233 ft)
tall stone statue, built between 713 and 803 (during the Tang Dynasty),
depicting Maitreya. It is carved out of a cliff face that lies at the
confluence of the Minjiang, Dadu and Qingyi rivers in the southern part
of Sichuan province in China, near the city of Leshan. The stone
sculpture faces Mount Emei, with the rivers flowing below his feet. It is
the largest stone Buddha in the world and it is by far the tallest
It is my hornor to invite you, your students and your friends to attend
this exhibition. For more information, please visit our official website
